The paper discusses nature-inspired algorithms for optimization problems, which are commonly studied in the subfield of computational intelligence (cs.NE). The paper also mentions the use of evolutionary algorithms and particle swarm optimization, which are subfields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the commonalities between these algorithms and more classical nature-inspired metaheuristics, which could fall under the subfields of control systems (cs.SY) or data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
